A  coalition of 27 global companies has asked Kenya to fully recognise the gay, lesbian, bisexual and transgender communities, to unlock billions for the economy. The coalition Open for Business, comprises Microsoft, Google, Barclays, Standard Chartered, Diageo, IBM, PwC, American Express, Burberry, among others. In a report titled, The Economic Case for LGBT+ Inclusion in Kenya, they say Kenya loses between U.S.$171 million and U.S.$1,2 billion every year because of policies that assign criminality and discriminate against members of the LGBTQ+ community, writes Elvis Ondieki for The Nation.